## Test 1: sync_update does NOT invalidate during streaming

This test verifies the `statusRef.current === 'streaming'` guard prevents premature history invalidation.

```typescript
it('does not call invalidateQueries on sync_update while streaming', async () => {
  mockUseRelayEnabled.mockReturnValue(true);
  vi.mocked(mockTransport.sendMessageRelay).mockResolvedValue({
    messageId: 'msg-1',
    traceId: 'trace-1',
  });

  // Use a real QueryClient so we can spy on invalidateQueries
  const queryClient = new QueryClient({
    defaultOptions: { queries: { retry: false } },
  });
  const invalidateSpy = vi.spyOn(queryClient, 'invalidateQueries');

  function WrapperWithQueryClient({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
    return React.createElement(
      QueryClientProvider,
      { client: queryClient },
      React.createElement(TransportProvider as any, { transport: mockTransport }, children)
    );
  }

  const { result } = renderHook(() => useChatSession('session-1'), {
    wrapper: WrapperWithQueryClient,
  });

  // Emit stream_ready so handleSubmit doesn't block on the 5s timeout
  act(() => {
    const es = MockEventSource.instances[0];
    es?.emit('stream_ready', { clientId: 'test-uuid-1' });
  });

  // Submit to put hook into 'streaming' state
  act(() => { result.current.setInput('hello'); });
  await act(async () => { await result.current.handleSubmit(); });

  // Confirm status is 'streaming'
  expect(result.current.status).toBe('streaming');

  // Clear any invalidations from the submit path
  invalidateSpy.mockClear();

  // Fire sync_update while streaming
  act(() => {
    const es = MockEventSource.instances[0];
    es?.emit('sync_update', {});
  });

  // invalidateQueries should NOT have been called — guard returns early
  expect(invalidateSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalled();
});
```

## Test 2: sync_update DOES invalidate after streaming completes

This test verifies history sync still works post-stream. Guards against overly aggressive fixes that skip all invalidation.

```typescript
it('calls invalidateQueries on sync_update when status is idle', async () => {
  mockUseRelayEnabled.mockReturnValue(true);

  // Use a real QueryClient so we can spy on invalidateQueries
  const queryClient = new QueryClient({
    defaultOptions: { queries: { retry: false } },
  });
  const invalidateSpy = vi.spyOn(queryClient, 'invalidateQueries');

  function WrapperWithQueryClient({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
    return React.createElement(
      QueryClientProvider,
      { client: queryClient },
      React.createElement(TransportProvider as any, { transport: mockTransport }, children)
    );
  }

  renderHook(() => useChatSession('session-1'), {
    wrapper: WrapperWithQueryClient,
  });

  // No submit — hook is in 'idle' state on mount
  // Clear any invalidations from mount/query setup
  invalidateSpy.mockClear();

  // Fire sync_update while idle
  act(() => {
    const es = MockEventSource.instances[0];
    es?.emit('sync_update', {});
  });

  // invalidateQueries SHOULD have been called — status is 'idle', guard does not return early
  expect(invalidateSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith(
    expect.objectContaining({
      queryKey: ['messages', 'session-1', expect.anything()],
    })
  );
});
```

## Existing test infrastructure to reuse

The test file already provides:
- `MockEventSource` class with `emit()` helper and `static instances[]`
- `createWrapper(transport)` factory (uses `new QueryClient` internally)
- `vi.mock('@/layers/entities/relay', ...)` for `mockUseRelayEnabled`
- `createMockTransport()` from `@dorkos/test-utils`

The new tests need their own `QueryClient` instances (to spy on `invalidateQueries`) rather than using `createWrapper()`. This is explicitly noted in the spec: "Client tests: `queryClient` should be a real `QueryClient` instance from `@tanstack/react-query` (not mocked), so `invalidateQueries` spy can be asserted".

## Acceptance Criteria

- Both tests pass with the guards from Tasks 1.1 and 1.2 in place
- Test 1 FAILS if the `if (statusRef.current === 'streaming') return;` guard is removed
- Test 2 FAILS if `invalidateQueries` is never called regardless of status
- No new mocks or test utilities are required beyond what already exists in the file
- Running `pnpm vitest run apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/__tests__/use-chat-session-relay.test.ts` passes all tests

